28// Adds S390-specific methods to convert InstructionOperands.
29class S390OperandConverter final : public InstructionOperandConverter {
30 public:
31 S390OperandConverter(CodeGenerator* gen, Instruction* instr)
32 : InstructionOperandConverter(gen, instr) {}
33
34 size_t OutputCount() { return instr_->OutputCount(); }
35
36 bool Is64BitOperand(int index) {
37 return LocationOperand::cast(instr_->InputAt(index))->representation() ==
38 MachineRepresentation::kWord64;
39 }
40
41 bool Is32BitOperand(int index) {
42 return LocationOperand::cast(instr_->InputAt(index))->representation() ==
43 MachineRepresentation::kWord32;
44 }
45
46 bool CompareLogical() const {
47 switch (instr_->flags_condition()) {
48 case kUnsignedLessThan:
49 case kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
50 case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
51 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
52 return true;
53 default:
54 return false;
55 }
56 UNREACHABLE();
57 }
58
59 Operand InputImmediate(size_t index) {
60 Constant constant = ToConstant(instr_->InputAt(index));
61 switch (constant.type()) {
62 case Constant::kInt32:
63 return Operand(constant.ToInt32());
64 case Constant::kFloat32:
65 return Operand::EmbeddedNumber(constant.ToFloat32());
66 case Constant::kFloat64:
67 return Operand::EmbeddedNumber(constant.ToFloat64().value());
68 case Constant::kInt64:
69 return Operand(constant.ToInt64());
70 case Constant::kExternalReference:
71 return Operand(constant.ToExternalReference());
72 case Constant::kCompressedHeapObject:
73 case Constant::kHeapObject:
74 case Constant::kRpoNumber:
75 break;
76 }
77 UNREACHABLE();
78 }
79
80 MemOperand MemoryOperand(AddressingMode* mode, size_t* first_index) {
81 const size_t index = *first_index;
82 if (mode) *mode = AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode());
83 switch (AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode())) {
84 case kMode_None:
85 break;
86 case kMode_MR:
87 *first_index += 1;
88 return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), 0);
89 case kMode_MRI:
90 *first_index += 2;
91 return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputInt32(index + 1));
92 case kMode_MRR:
93 *first_index += 2;
94 return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputRegister(index + 1));
95 case kMode_MRRI:
96 *first_index += 3;
97 return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputRegister(index + 1),
98 InputInt32(index + 2));
99 case kMode_Root:
100 *first_index += 1;
101 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, InputInt32(index));
102 }
103 UNREACHABLE();
104 }
105
106 MemOperand MemoryOperand(AddressingMode* mode = nullptr,
107 size_t first_index = 0) {
108 return MemoryOperand(mode, &first_index);
109 }
110
111 MemOperand ToMemOperand(InstructionOperand* op) const {
112 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(op);
113 DCHECK(op->IsStackSlot() || op->IsFPStackSlot());
114 return SlotToMemOperand(AllocatedOperand::cast(op)->index());
115 }
116
117 MemOperand SlotToMemOperand(int slot) const {
118 FrameOffset offset = frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(slot);
119 return MemOperand(offset.from_stack_pointer() ? sp : fp, offset.offset());
120 }
121
122 MemOperand InputStackSlot(size_t index) {
123 InstructionOperand* op = instr_->InputAt(index);
124 return SlotToMemOperand(AllocatedOperand::cast(op)->index());
125 }
126
127 MemOperand InputStackSlot32(size_t index) {
128#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_S390X && !V8_TARGET_LITTLE_ENDIAN
129 // We want to read the 32-bits directly from memory
130 MemOperand mem = InputStackSlot(index);
131 return MemOperand(mem.rx(), mem.rb(), mem.offset() + 4);
132#else
133 return InputStackSlot(index);
134#endif
135 }
136};
137
138static inline bool HasRegisterOutput(Instruction* instr, int index = 0) {
139 return instr->OutputCount() > 0 && instr->OutputAt(index)->IsRegister();
140}
141
142static inline bool HasFPRegisterInput(Instruction* instr, int index) {
143 return instr->InputAt(index)->IsFPRegister();
144}
145
146static inline bool HasRegisterInput(Instruction* instr, int index) {
147 return instr->InputAt(index)->IsRegister() ||
148 HasFPRegisterInput(instr, index);
149}
150
151static inline bool HasImmediateInput(Instruction* instr, size_t index) {
152 return instr->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate();
153}
154
155static inline bool HasFPStackSlotInput(Instruction* instr, size_t index) {
156 return instr->InputAt(index)->IsFPStackSlot();
157}
158
159static inline bool HasStackSlotInput(Instruction* instr, size_t index) {
160 return instr->InputAt(index)->IsStackSlot() ||
161 HasFPStackSlotInput(instr, index);
162}

166class OutOfLineRecordWrite final : public OutOfLineCode {
167 public:
168 OutOfLineRecordWrite(CodeGenerator* gen, Register object, MemOperand operand,
169 Register value, Register scratch0, Register scratch1,
170 RecordWriteMode mode, StubCallMode stub_mode,
171 UnwindingInfoWriter* unwinding_info_writer)
172 : OutOfLineCode(gen),
173 object_(object),
174 operand_(operand),
175 value_(value),
176 scratch0_(scratch0),
177 scratch1_(scratch1),
178 mode_(mode),
179#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
180 stub_mode_(stub_mode),
181#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
182 must_save_lr_(!gen->frame_access_state()->has_frame()),
183 unwinding_info_writer_(unwinding_info_writer),
184 zone_(gen->zone()) {
185 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, scratch0, scratch1));
186 DCHECK(!AreAliased(value, scratch0, scratch1));
187 }
188
189 void Generate() final {
190 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
191 __ DecompressTagged(value_, value_);
192 }
193 __ CheckPageFlag(value_, scratch0_,
194 MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq,
195 exit());
196 __ lay(scratch1_, operand_);
197 SaveFPRegsMode const save_fp_mode = frame()->DidAllocateDoubleRegisters()
198 ? SaveFPRegsMode::kSave
199 : SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore;
200 if (must_save_lr_) {
201 // We need to save and restore r14 if the frame was elided.
202 __ Push(r14);
203 unwinding_info_writer_->MarkLinkRegisterOnTopOfStack(__ pc_offset());
204 }
205 if (mode_ == RecordWriteMode::kValueIsEphemeronKey) {
206 __ CallEphemeronKeyBarrier(object_, scratch1_, save_fp_mode);
207#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
208 } else if (stub_mode_ == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
209 __ CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object_, scratch1_, save_fp_mode,
210 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
211#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
212 } else {
213 __ CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object_, scratch1_, save_fp_mode);
214 }
215 if (must_save_lr_) {
216 // We need to save and restore r14 if the frame was elided.
217 __ Pop(r14);
218 unwinding_info_writer_->MarkPopLinkRegisterFromTopOfStack(__ pc_offset());
219 }
220 }
221
222 private:
223 Register const object_;
224 MemOperand const operand_;
225 Register const value_;
226 Register const scratch0_;
227 Register const scratch1_;
228 RecordWriteMode const mode_;
229#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
230 StubCallMode stub_mode_;
231#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
232 bool must_save_lr_;
233 UnwindingInfoWriter* const unwinding_info_writer_;
234 Zone* zone_;
235};

237Condition FlagsConditionToCondition(FlagsCondition condition, ArchOpcode op) {
238 switch (condition) {
239 case kEqual:
240 return eq;
241 case kNotEqual:
242 return ne;
243 case kUnsignedLessThan:
244 // unsigned number never less than 0
245 if (op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord32 || op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord64)
246 return CC_NOP;
247 [[fallthrough]];
248 case kSignedLessThan:
249 return lt;
250 case kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
251 // unsigned number always greater than or equal 0
252 if (op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord32 || op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord64)
253 return CC_ALWAYS;
254 [[fallthrough]];
255 case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
256 return ge;
257 case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
258 // unsigned number never less than 0
259 if (op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord32 || op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord64)
260 return CC_EQ;
261 [[fallthrough]];
262 case kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
263 return le;
264 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
265 // unsigned number always greater than or equal 0
266 if (op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord32 || op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord64)
267 return ne;
268 [[fallthrough]];
269 case kSignedGreaterThan:
270 return gt;
271 case kOverflow:
272 // Overflow checked for AddS64/SubS64 only.
273 switch (op) {
274 case kS390_Add32:
275 case kS390_Add64:
276 case kS390_Sub32:
277 case kS390_Sub64:
278 case kS390_Abs64:
279 case kS390_Abs32:
280 case kS390_Mul32:
281 case kS390_Mul64WithOverflow:
282 return overflow;
283 default:
284 break;
285 }
286 break;
287 case kNotOverflow:
288 switch (op) {
289 case kS390_Add32:
290 case kS390_Add64:
291 case kS390_Sub32:
292 case kS390_Sub64:
293 case kS390_Abs64:
294 case kS390_Abs32:
295 case kS390_Mul32:
296 case kS390_Mul64WithOverflow:
297 return nooverflow;
298 default:
299 break;
300 }
301 break;
302 default:
303 break;
304 }
305 UNREACHABLE();
306}

437template <int numOfOperand, class RType, class MType, class IType>
438static inline int AssembleOp(Instruction* instr, RType r, MType m, IType i) {
439 AddressingMode mode = AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode());
440 if (mode != kMode_None || HasStackSlotInput(instr, numOfOperand - 1)) {
441 return m();
442 } else if (HasRegisterInput(instr, numOfOperand - 1)) {
443 return r();
444 } else if (HasImmediateInput(instr, numOfOperand - 1)) {
445 return i();
446 } else {
447 UNREACHABLE();
448 }
449}

451template <class _RR, class _RM, class _RI>
452static inline int AssembleBinOp(Instruction* instr, _RR _rr, _RM _rm, _RI _ri) {
453 return AssembleOp<2>(instr, _rr, _rm, _ri);
454}

456template <class _R, class _M, class _I>
457static inline int AssembleUnaryOp(Instruction* instr, _R _r, _M _m, _I _i) {
458 return AssembleOp<1>(instr, _r, _m, _i);
459}

487#define ASSEMBLE_COMPARE(cmp_instr, cmpl_instr) \
488 do { \
489 AddressingMode mode = AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode()); \
490 if (mode != kMode_None) { \
491 size_t first_index = 1; \
492 MemOperand operand = i.MemoryOperand(&mode, &first_index); \
493 if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
494 __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), operand); \
495 } else { \
496 __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), operand); \
497 } \
498 } else if (HasRegisterInput(instr, 1)) { \
499 if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
500 __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
501 } else { \
502 __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
503 } \
504 } else if (HasImmediateInput(instr, 1)) { \
505 if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
506 __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputImmediate(1)); \
507 } else { \
508 __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputImmediate(1)); \
509 } \
510 } else { \
511 DCHECK(HasStackSlotInput(instr, 1)); \
512 if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
513 __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputStackSlot(1)); \
514 } else { \
515 __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputStackSlot(1)); \
516 } \
517 } \
518 } while (0)

646#define ASSEMBLE_LOADANDTEST64(asm_instr_rr, asm_instr_rm) \
647 { \
648 AddressingMode mode = AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode()); \
649 Register dst = HasRegisterOutput(instr) ? i.OutputRegister() : r0; \
650 if (mode != kMode_None) { \
651 size_t first_index = 0; \

659 } \

829#define ATOMIC_BIN_OP(bin_inst, offset, shift_amount, start, end, \
830 maybe_reverse_bytes) \
831 do { \
832 /* At the moment this is only true when dealing with 2-byte values.*/ \
833 bool reverse_bytes = maybe_reverse_bytes && is_wasm_on_be(info()); \
834 USE(reverse_bytes); \
835 Label do_cs; \
836 __ LoadU32(prev, MemOperand(addr, offset)); \
837 __ bind(&do_cs); \
838 if (reverse_bytes) { \
839 Register temp2 = GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(value, result, prev); \
840 __ Push(temp2); \
841 __ lrvr(temp2, prev); \
842 __ RotateInsertSelectBits(temp2, temp2, Operand(start), Operand(end), \
843 Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(shift_amount)), \
844 true); \
845 __ RotateInsertSelectBits(temp, value, Operand(start), Operand(end), \
846 Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(shift_amount)), \
847 true); \
848 __ bin_inst(new_val, temp2, temp); \
849 __ lrvr(temp2, new_val); \
850 __ lr(temp, prev); \
851 __ RotateInsertSelectBits(temp, temp2, Operand(start), Operand(end), \
852 Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(shift_amount)), \
853 false); \
854 __ Pop(temp2); \
855 } else { \
856 __ RotateInsertSelectBits(temp, value, Operand(start), Operand(end), \
857 Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(shift_amount)), \
858 true); \
859 __ bin_inst(new_val, prev, temp); \
860 __ lr(temp, prev); \
861 __ RotateInsertSelectBits(temp, new_val, Operand(start), Operand(end), \
862 Operand::Zero(), false); \
863 } \
864 __ CmpAndSwap(prev, temp, MemOperand(addr, offset)); \
865 __ bne(&do_cs, Label::kNear); \
866 } while (false)

997void FlushPendingPushRegisters(MacroAssembler* masm,
998 FrameAccessState* frame_access_state,
999 ZoneVector<Register>* pending_pushes) {
1000 switch (pending_pushes->size()) {
1001 case 0:
1002 break;
1003 case 1:
1004 masm->Push((*pending_pushes)[0]);
1005 break;
1006 case 2:
1007 masm->Push((*pending_pushes)[0], (*pending_pushes)[1]);
1008 break;
1009 case 3:
1010 masm->Push((*pending_pushes)[0], (*pending_pushes)[1],
1011 (*pending_pushes)[2]);
1012 break;
1013 default:
1014 UNREACHABLE();
1015 }
1016 frame_access_state->IncreaseSPDelta(pending_pushes->size());
1017 pending_pushes->clear();
1018}
1019
1020void AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(
1021 MacroAssembler* masm, FrameAccessState* state, int new_slot_above_sp,
1022 ZoneVector<Register>* pending_pushes = nullptr,
1023 bool allow_shrinkage = true) {
1024 int current_sp_offset = state->GetSPToFPSlotCount() +
1025 StandardFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCountAboveFp;
1026 int stack_slot_delta = new_slot_above_sp - current_sp_offset;
1027 if (stack_slot_delta > 0) {
1028 if (pending_pushes != nullptr) {
1029 FlushPendingPushRegisters(masm, state, pending_pushes);
1030 }
1031 masm->AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(-stack_slot_delta * kSystemPointerSize));
1032 state->IncreaseSPDelta(stack_slot_delta);
1033 } else if (allow_shrinkage && stack_slot_delta < 0) {
1034 if (pending_pushes != nullptr) {
1035 FlushPendingPushRegisters(masm, state, pending_pushes);
1036 }
1037 masm->AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(-stack_slot_delta * kSystemPointerSize));
1038 state->IncreaseSPDelta(stack_slot_delta);
1039 }
1040}

1044void CodeGenerator::AssembleTailCallBeforeGap(Instruction* instr,
1045 int first_unused_slot_offset) {
1046 ZoneVector<MoveOperands*> pushes(zone());
1047 GetPushCompatibleMoves(instr, kRegisterPush, &pushes);
1048
1049 if (!pushes.empty() &&
1050 (LocationOperand::cast(pushes.back()->destination()).index() + 1 ==
1051 first_unused_slot_offset)) {
1052 S390OperandConverter g(this, instr);
1053 ZoneVector<Register> pending_pushes(zone());
1054 for (auto move : pushes) {
1055 LocationOperand destination_location(
1056 LocationOperand::cast(move->destination()));
1057 InstructionOperand source(move->source());
1058 AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(
1059 masm(), frame_access_state(),
1060 destination_location.index() - pending_pushes.size(),
1061 &pending_pushes);
1062 // Pushes of non-register data types are not supported.
1063 DCHECK(source.IsRegister());
1064 LocationOperand source_location(LocationOperand::cast(source));
1065 pending_pushes.push_back(source_location.GetRegister());
1066 // TODO(arm): We can push more than 3 registers at once. Add support in
1067 // the macro-assembler for pushing a list of registers.
1068 if (pending_pushes.size() == 3) {
1069 FlushPendingPushRegisters(masm(), frame_access_state(),
1070 &pending_pushes);
1071 }
1072 move->Eliminate();
1073 }
1074 FlushPendingPushRegisters(masm(), frame_access_state(), &pending_pushes);
1075 }
1076 AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(masm(), frame_access_state(),
1077 first_unused_slot_offset, nullptr, false);
1078}
1079
1080void CodeGenerator::AssembleTailCallAfterGap(Instruction* instr,
1081 int first_unused_slot_offset) {
1082 AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(masm(), frame_access_state(),
1083 first_unused_slot_offset);
1084}

1104// Assembles an instruction after register allocation, producing machine code.
1105CodeGenerator::CodeGenResult CodeGenerator::AssembleArchInstruction(
1106 Instruction* instr) {
1107 S390OperandConverter i(this, instr);
1108 ArchOpcode opcode = ArchOpcodeField::decode(instr->opcode());
1109
1110 switch (opcode) {
1111 case kArchComment:
1112 __ RecordComment(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(i.InputInt64(0)),
1113 SourceLocation());
1114 break;
1115 case kArchCallCodeObject: {
1116 if (HasRegisterInput(instr, 0)) {
1117 Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
1118 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
1119 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
1120 reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
1121 __ CallCodeObject(reg);
1122 } else {
1123 __ Call(i.InputCode(0), RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
1124 }
1125 RecordCallPosition(instr);
1126 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1127 break;
1128 }
1129 case kArchCallBuiltinPointer: {
1130 DCHECK(!instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate());
1131 Register builtin_index = i.InputRegister(0);
1132 Register target =
1133 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister)
1134 ? kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister
1135 : builtin_index;
1136 __ CallBuiltinByIndex(builtin_index, target);
1137 RecordCallPosition(instr);
1138 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1139 break;
1140 }
1141#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1142 case kArchCallWasmFunction:
1143 case kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect: {
1144 // We must not share code targets for calls to builtins for wasm code, as
1145 // they might need to be patched individually.
1146 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
1147 DCHECK_EQ(opcode, kArchCallWasmFunction);
1148 Constant constant = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(0));
1149 Address wasm_code = static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64());
1150 __ Call(wasm_code, constant.rmode());
1151 } else if (opcode == kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect) {
1152 __ CallWasmCodePointer(i.InputRegister(0));
1153 } else {
1154 __ Call(i.InputRegister(0));
1155 }
1156 RecordCallPosition(instr);
1157 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1158 break;
1159 }
1160 case kArchTailCallWasm:
1161 case kArchTailCallWasmIndirect: {
1162 // We must not share code targets for calls to builtins for wasm code, as
1163 // they might need to be patched individually.
1164 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
1165 DCHECK_EQ(opcode, kArchTailCallWasm);
1166 Constant constant = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(0));
1167 Address wasm_code = static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64());
1168 __ Jump(wasm_code, constant.rmode());
1169 } else if (opcode == kArchTailCallWasmIndirect) {
1170 __ CallWasmCodePointer(i.InputRegister(0), CallJumpMode::kTailCall);
1171 } else {
1172 __ Jump(i.InputRegister(0));
1173 }
1174 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1175 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
1176 break;
1177 }
1178#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1179 case kArchTailCallCodeObject: {
1180 if (HasRegisterInput(instr, 0)) {
1181 Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
1182 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
1183 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
1184 reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
1185 __ JumpCodeObject(reg);
1186 } else {
1187 // We cannot use the constant pool to load the target since
1188 // we've already restored the caller's frame.
1189 ConstantPoolUnavailableScope constant_pool_unavailable(masm());
1190 __ Jump(i.InputCode(0), RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
1191 }
1192 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1193 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
1194 break;
1195 }
1196 case kArchTailCallAddress: {
1197 CHECK(!instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate());
1198 Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
1199 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
1200 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
1201 reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
1202 __ Jump(reg);
1203 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1204 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
1205 break;
1206 }
1207 case kArchCallJSFunction: {
1208 Register func = i.InputRegister(0);
1209 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
1210 // Check the function's context matches the context argument.
1211 __ LoadTaggedField(kScratchReg,
1212 FieldMemOperand(func, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
1213 __ CmpS64(cp, kScratchReg);
1214 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kWrongFunctionContext);
1215 }
1216 uint32_t num_arguments =
1217 i.InputUint32(instr->JSCallArgumentCountInputIndex());
1218 __ CallJSFunction(func, num_arguments);
1219 RecordCallPosition(instr);
1220 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1221 break;
1222 }
1223 case kArchPrepareCallCFunction: {
1224 int const num_gp_parameters = ParamField::decode(instr->opcode());
1225 int const num_fp_parameters = FPParamField::decode(instr->opcode());
1226 __ PrepareCallCFunction(num_gp_parameters + num_fp_parameters,
1227 kScratchReg);
1228 // Frame alignment requires using FP-relative frame addressing.
1229 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToFP();
1230 break;
1231 }
1232 case kArchSaveCallerRegisters: {
1233 fp_mode_ =
1234 static_cast<SaveFPRegsMode>(MiscField::decode(instr->opcode()));
1235 DCHECK(fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore ||
1236 fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave);
1237 // kReturnRegister0 should have been saved before entering the stub.
1238 int bytes = __ PushCallerSaved(fp_mode_, ip, kReturnRegister0);
1239 DCHECK(IsAligned(bytes, kSystemPointerSize));
1240 DCHECK_EQ(0, frame_access_state()->sp_delta());
1241 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(bytes / kSystemPointerSize);
1242 DCHECK(!caller_registers_saved_);

1244 break;
1245 }
1246 case kArchRestoreCallerRegisters: {
1247 DCHECK(fp_mode_ ==
1248 static_cast<SaveFPRegsMode>(MiscField::decode(instr->opcode())));
1249 DCHECK(fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore ||
1250 fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave);
1251 // Don't overwrite the returned value.
1252 int bytes = __ PopCallerSaved(fp_mode_, ip, kReturnRegister0);
1253 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-(bytes / kSystemPointerSize));
1254 DCHECK_EQ(0, frame_access_state()->sp_delta());
1255 DCHECK(caller_registers_saved_);
1256 caller_registers_saved_ = false;
1257 break;
1258 }

1260 AssemblePrepareTailCall();

1262 case kArchCallCFunctionWithFrameState:
1263 case kArchCallCFunction: {
1264 int const num_gp_parameters = ParamField::decode(instr->opcode());
1265 int const fp_param_field = FPParamField::decode(instr->opcode());
1266 int num_fp_parameters = fp_param_field;
1267 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots = SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes;
1268 Label return_location;
1269 bool has_function_descriptor = false;
1270#if ABI_USES_FUNCTION_DESCRIPTORS
1271 int kNumFPParametersMask = kHasFunctionDescriptorBitMask - 1;
1272 num_fp_parameters = kNumFPParametersMask & fp_param_field;
1273 has_function_descriptor =
1274 (fp_param_field & kHasFunctionDescriptorBitMask) != 0;
1275#endif
1276 // Put the return address in a stack slot.
1277#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1278 if (linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor()->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
1279 // Put the return address in a stack slot.
1280 __ larl(r0, &return_location);
1281 __ StoreU64(r0,
1282 MemOperand(fp, WasmExitFrameConstants::kCallingPCOffset));
1283 set_isolate_data_slots = SetIsolateDataSlots::kNo;
1284 }
1285#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1286 int pc_offset;
1287 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
1288 ExternalReference ref = i.InputExternalReference(0);
1289 pc_offset = __ CallCFunction(ref, num_gp_parameters, num_fp_parameters,
1290 set_isolate_data_slots,
1291 has_function_descriptor, &return_location);
1292 } else {
1293 Register func = i.InputRegister(0);
1294 pc_offset = __ CallCFunction(func, num_gp_parameters, num_fp_parameters,
1295 set_isolate_data_slots,
1296 has_function_descriptor, &return_location);
1297 }
1298 RecordSafepoint(instr->reference_map(), pc_offset);
1299
1300 bool const needs_frame_state =
1301 (opcode == kArchCallCFunctionWithFrameState);
1302 if (needs_frame_state) {
1303 RecordDeoptInfo(instr, pc_offset);
1304 }
1305
1306 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
1307 // Ideally, we should decrement SP delta to match the change of stack
1308 // pointer in CallCFunction. However, for certain architectures (e.g.
1309 // ARM), there may be more strict alignment requirement, causing old SP
1310 // to be saved on the stack. In those cases, we can not calculate the SP
1311 // delta statically.
1312 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1313 if (caller_registers_saved_) {
1314 // Need to re-sync SP delta introduced in kArchSaveCallerRegisters.
1315 // Here, we assume the sequence to be:
1316 // kArchSaveCallerRegisters;
1317 // kArchCallCFunction;
1318 // kArchRestoreCallerRegisters;
1319 int bytes =
1320 __ RequiredStackSizeForCallerSaved(fp_mode_, kReturnRegister0);
1321 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(bytes / kSystemPointerSize);
1322 }
1323 break;
1324 }

1958 case kS390_Push: {
1959 int stack_decrement = i.InputInt32(0);
1960 int slots = stack_decrement / kSystemPointerSize;
1961 LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(instr->InputAt(1));
1962 MachineRepresentation rep = op->representation();
1963 int pushed_slots = ElementSizeInPointers(rep);
1964 // Slot-sized arguments are never padded but there may be a gap if
1965 // the slot allocator reclaimed other padding slots. Adjust the stack
1966 // here to skip any gap.
1967 __ AllocateStackSpace((slots - pushed_slots) * kSystemPointerSize);
1968 switch (rep) {
1969 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1970 __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kSystemPointerSize));
1971 __ StoreF32(i.InputDoubleRegister(1), MemOperand(sp));
1972 break;
1973 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1974 __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kDoubleSize));
1975 __ StoreF64(i.InputDoubleRegister(1), MemOperand(sp));
1976 break;
1977 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1978 __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kSimd128Size));
1979 __ StoreV128(i.InputDoubleRegister(1), MemOperand(sp), kScratchReg);
1980 break;
1981 default:
1982 __ Push(i.InputRegister(1));
1983 break;
1984 }
1985 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(slots);
1986 break;

2387 MemOperand mem = i.MemoryOperand();
2388 if (!is_int20(mem.offset())) {
2389 // Add directly to the base register in case the index register (rx) is
2390 // r0.
2391 DCHECK(is_int32(mem.offset()));
2392 __ AddS64(ip, mem.rb(), Operand(mem.offset()));
2393 mem = MemOperand(mem.rx(), ip);
2394 }
2395 __ lay(i.OutputRegister(), mem);
2396 break;
2397 }
2398 case kAtomicExchangeInt8:
2399 case kAtomicExchangeUint8: {
2400 Register base = i.InputRegister(0);
2401 Register index = i.InputRegister(1);
2402 Register value = i.InputRegister(2);
2403 Register output = i.OutputRegister();
2404 __ la(r1, MemOperand(base, index));
2405 __ AtomicExchangeU8(r1, value, output, r0);
2406 if (opcode == kAtomicExchangeInt8) {
2407 __ LoadS8(output, output);
2408 } else {
2409 __ LoadU8(output, output);
2410 }
2411 break;
2412 }
2413 case kAtomicExchangeInt16:
2414 case kAtomicExchangeUint16: {
2415 Register base = i.InputRegister(0);
2416 Register index = i.InputRegister(1);
2417 Register value = i.InputRegister(2);
2418 Register output = i.OutputRegister();
2419 bool reverse_bytes = is_wasm_on_be(info());
2420 __ la(r1, MemOperand(base, index));
2421 Register value_ = value;
2422 if (reverse_bytes) {
2423 value_ = ip;
2424 __ lrvr(value_, value);
2425 __ ShiftRightU32(value_, value_, Operand(16));
2426 }
2427 __ AtomicExchangeU16(r1, value_, output, r0);
2428 if (reverse_bytes) {
2429 __ lrvr(output, output);
2430 __ ShiftRightU32(output, output, Operand(16));
2431 }
2432 if (opcode == kAtomicExchangeInt16) {
2433 __ lghr(output, output);
2434 } else {
2435 __ llghr(output, output);
2436 }
2437 break;
2438 }
2439 case kAtomicExchangeWord32: {
2440 Register base = i.InputRegister(0);
2441 Register index = i.InputRegister(1);
2442 Register value = i.InputRegister(2);
2443 Register output = i.OutputRegister();
2444 Label do_cs;
2445 bool reverse_bytes = is_wasm_on_be(info());
2446 __ lay(r1, MemOperand(base, index));
2447 Register value_ = value;
2448 if (reverse_bytes) {
2449 value_ = ip;
2450 __ lrvr(value_, value);
2451 }
2452 __ LoadU32(output, MemOperand(r1));
2453 __ bind(&do_cs);
2454 __ cs(output, value_, MemOperand(r1));
2455 __ bne(&do_cs, Label::kNear);
2456 if (reverse_bytes) {
2457 __ lrvr(output, output);
2458 __ LoadU32(output, output);
2459 }
2460 break;
2461 }
2462 case kAtomicCompareExchangeInt8:
2463 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_BYTE(LoadS8);
2464 break;
2465 case kAtomicCompareExchangeUint8:
2466 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_BYTE(LoadU8);
2467 break;
2468 case kAtomicCompareExchangeInt16:
2469 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(LoadS16);
2470 break;
2471 case kAtomicCompareExchangeUint16:
2472 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(LoadU16);
2473 break;
2474 case kAtomicCompareExchangeWord32:
2475 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_WORD();
2476 break;
2477#define ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(op, inst) \
2478 case kAtomic##op##Int8: \
2479 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_BYTE(inst, [&]() { \
2480 intptr_t shift_right = static_cast<intptr_t>(shift_amount); \
2481 __ srlk(result, prev, Operand(shift_right)); \
2482 __ LoadS8(result, result); \
2483 }); \
2484 break; \
2485 case kAtomic##op##Uint8: \
2486 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_BYTE(inst, [&]() { \
2487 int rotate_left = shift_amount == 0 ? 0 : 64 - shift_amount; \
2488 __ RotateInsertSelectBits(result, prev, Operand(56), Operand(63), \
2489 Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(rotate_left)), \
2490 true); \
2491 }); \
2492 break; \
2493 case kAtomic##op##Int16: \
2494 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_HALFWORD(inst, [&]() { \
2495 intptr_t shift_right = static_cast<intptr_t>(shift_amount); \
2496 __ srlk(result, prev, Operand(shift_right)); \
2497 if (is_wasm_on_be(info())) { \
2498 __ lrvr(result, result); \
2499 __ ShiftRightS32(result, result, Operand(16)); \
2500 } \
2501 __ LoadS16(result, result); \
2502 }); \
2503 break; \
2504 case kAtomic##op##Uint16: \
2505 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_HALFWORD(inst, [&]() { \
2506 int rotate_left = shift_amount == 0 ? 0 : 64 - shift_amount; \
2507 __ RotateInsertSelectBits(result, prev, Operand(48), Operand(63), \
2508 Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(rotate_left)), \
2509 true); \
2510 if (is_wasm_on_be(info())) { \
2511 __ lrvr(result, result); \
2512 __ ShiftRightU32(result, result, Operand(16)); \
2513 } \
2514 }); \
2515 break;
2516 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Add, AddS32)
2517 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Sub, SubS32)
2518 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(And, And)
2519 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Or, Or)
2520 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Xor, Xor)
2521#undef ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE
2522 case kAtomicAddWord32:
2523 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_WORD(laa, AddS32);
2524 break;
2525 case kAtomicSubWord32:
2526 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_WORD(LoadAndSub32, SubS32);
2527 break;
2528 case kAtomicAndWord32:
2529 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_WORD(lan, AndP);
2530 break;
2531 case kAtomicOrWord32:
2532 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_WORD(lao, OrP);
2533 break;
2534 case kAtomicXorWord32:
2535 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_WORD(lax, XorP);
2536 break;
2537 case kS390_Word64AtomicAddUint64:
2538 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_WORD64(laag, AddS64);
2539 break;
2540 case kS390_Word64AtomicSubUint64:
2541 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_WORD64(LoadAndSub64, SubS64);
2542 break;
2543 case kS390_Word64AtomicAndUint64:
2544 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_WORD64(lang, AndP);
2545 break;
2546 case kS390_Word64AtomicOrUint64:
2547 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_WORD64(laog, OrP);
2548 break;
2549 case kS390_Word64AtomicXorUint64:
2550 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_WORD64(laxg, XorP);
2551 break;
2552 case kS390_Word64AtomicExchangeUint64: {
2553 Register base = i.InputRegister(0);
2554 Register index = i.InputRegister(1);
2555 Register value = i.InputRegister(2);
2556 Register output = i.OutputRegister();
2557 bool reverse_bytes = is_wasm_on_be(info());
2558 Label do_cs;
2559 Register value_ = value;
2560 __ la(r1, MemOperand(base, index));
2561 if (reverse_bytes) {
2562 value_ = ip;
2563 __ lrvgr(value_, value);
2564 }
2565 __ lg(output, MemOperand(r1));
2566 __ bind(&do_cs);
2567 __ csg(output, value_, MemOperand(r1));
2568 __ bne(&do_cs, Label::kNear);
2569 if (reverse_bytes) {
2570 __ lrvgr(output, output);
2571 }
2572 break;
2573 }
2574 case kS390_Word64AtomicCompareExchangeUint64:
2575 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC64_COMP_EXCHANGE_WORD64();
2576 break;

3200// Assembles branches after an instruction.
3201void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBranch(Instruction* instr, BranchInfo* branch) {
3202 S390OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3203 Label* tlabel = branch->true_label;
3204 Label* flabel = branch->false_label;
3205 ArchOpcode op = instr->arch_opcode();
3206 FlagsCondition condition = branch->condition;
3207
3208 Condition cond = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition, op);
3209 if (op == kS390_CmpFloat || op == kS390_CmpDouble) {
3210 // check for unordered if necessary
3211 // Branching to flabel/tlabel according to what's expected by tests
3212 if (cond == le || cond == eq || cond == lt) {
3213 __ bunordered(flabel);
3214 } else if (cond == gt || cond == ne || cond == ge) {
3215 __ bunordered(tlabel);
3216 }
3217 }
3218 __ b(cond, tlabel);
3219 if (!branch->fallthru) __ b(flabel); // no fallthru to flabel.
3220}

3284// Assembles boolean materializations after an instruction.
3285void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBoolean(Instruction* instr,
3286 FlagsCondition condition) {
3287 S390OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3288 ArchOpcode op = instr->arch_opcode();
3289 bool check_unordered = (op == kS390_CmpDouble || op == kS390_CmpFloat);
3290
3291 // Overflow checked for add/sub only.
3292 DCHECK((condition != kOverflow && condition != kNotOverflow) ||
3293 (op == kS390_Add32 || op == kS390_Add64 || op == kS390_Sub32 ||
3294 op == kS390_Sub64 || op == kS390_Mul32 ||
3295 op == kS390_Mul64WithOverflow));
3296
3297 // Materialize a full 32-bit 1 or 0 value. The result register is always the
3298 // last output of the instruction.
3299 DCHECK_NE(0u, instr->OutputCount());
3300 Register reg = i.OutputRegister(instr->OutputCount() - 1);
3301 Condition cond = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition, op);
3302 Label done;
3303 if (check_unordered) {
3304 __ mov(reg, (cond == eq || cond == le || cond == lt) ? Operand::Zero()
3305 : Operand(1));
3306 __ bunordered(&done);
3307 }
3308
3309 // TODO(john.yan): use load imm high on condition here
3310 __ mov(reg, Operand::Zero());
3311 __ mov(kScratchReg, Operand(1));
3312 // locr is sufficient since reg's upper 32 is guarrantee to be 0
3313 __ locr(cond, reg, kScratchReg);
3314 __ bind(&done);
3315}

3337void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchTableSwitch(Instruction* instr) {
3338 S390OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3339 Register input = i.InputRegister(0);
3340 int32_t const case_count = static_cast<int32_t>(instr->InputCount() - 2);
3341 base::Vector<Label*> cases = zone()->AllocateVector<Label*>(case_count);
3342 for (int32_t index = 0; index < case_count; ++index) {
3343 cases[index] = GetLabel(i.InputRpo(index + 2));
3344 }
3345 Label* const table = AddJumpTable(cases);
3346 __ CmpU64(input, Operand(case_count));
3347 __ bge(GetLabel(i.InputRpo(1)));
3348 __ larl(kScratchReg, table);
3349 __ ShiftLeftU64(r1, input, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
3350 __ LoadU64(kScratchReg, MemOperand(kScratchReg, r1));
3351 __ Jump(kScratchReg);
3352}

3359void CodeGenerator::FinishFrame(Frame* frame) {
3360 auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
3361 const DoubleRegList double_saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters();
3362
3363 // Save callee-saved Double registers.
3364 if (!double_saves.is_empty()) {
3365 frame->AlignSavedCalleeRegisterSlots();
3366 DCHECK_EQ(kNumCalleeSavedDoubles, double_saves.Count());
3367 frame->AllocateSavedCalleeRegisterSlots(kNumCalleeSavedDoubles *
3368 (kDoubleSize / kSystemPointerSize));
3369 }
3370 // Save callee-saved registers.
3371 const RegList saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters();
3372 if (!saves.is_empty()) {
3373 // register save area does not include the fp or constant pool pointer.
3374 const int num_saves = kNumCalleeSaved - 1;
3375 frame->AllocateSavedCalleeRegisterSlots(num_saves);
3376 }
3377}
3378
3379void CodeGenerator::AssembleConstructFrame() {
3380 auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
3381
3382 if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
3383 if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
3384#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3385 if (info()->GetOutputStackFrameType() == StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY) {
3386 __ StubPrologue(StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY);
3387 // Reserve stack space for saving the c_entry_fp later.
3388 __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kSystemPointerSize));
3389#else
3390 // For balance.
3391 if (false) {
3392#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3393 } else {
3394 __ Push(r14, fp);
3395 __ mov(fp, sp);
3396 }
3397 } else if (call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall()) {
3398 __ Prologue(ip);
3399 } else {
3400 StackFrame::Type type = info()->GetOutputStackFrameType();
3401 // TODO(mbrandy): Detect cases where ip is the entrypoint (for
3402 // efficient initialization of the constant pool pointer register).
3403 __ StubPrologue(type);
3404#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3405 if (call_descriptor->IsAnyWasmFunctionCall() ||
3406 call_descriptor->IsWasmImportWrapper() ||
3407 call_descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
3408 // For import wrappers and C-API functions, this stack slot is only used
3409 // for printing stack traces in V8. Also, it holds a WasmImportData
3410 // instead of the trusted instance data, which is taken care of in the
3411 // frames accessors.
3412 __ Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
3413 }
3414 if (call_descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
3415 // Reserve space for saving the PC later.
3416 __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kSystemPointerSize));
3417 }
3418#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3419 }
3420 unwinding_info_writer_.MarkFrameConstructed(__ pc_offset());
3421 }
3422
3423 int required_slots =
3424 frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - frame()->GetFixedSlotCount();
3425 if (info()->is_osr()) {
3426 // TurboFan OSR-compiled functions cannot be entered directly.
3427 __ Abort(AbortReason::kShouldNotDirectlyEnterOsrFunction);
3428
3429 // Unoptimized code jumps directly to this entrypoint while the unoptimized
3430 // frame is still on the stack. Optimized code uses OSR values directly from
3431 // the unoptimized frame. Thus, all that needs to be done is to allocate the
3432 // remaining stack slots.
3433 __ RecordComment("-- OSR entrypoint --");
3434 osr_pc_offset_ = __ pc_offset();
3435 required_slots -= osr_helper()->UnoptimizedFrameSlots();
3436 }
3437
3438 const DoubleRegList saves_fp = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters();
3439 const RegList saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters();
3440
3441 if (required_slots > 0) {
3442#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3443 if (info()->IsWasm() && required_slots * kSystemPointerSize > 4 * KB) {
3444 // For WebAssembly functions with big frames we have to do the stack
3445 // overflow check before we construct the frame. Otherwise we may not
3446 // have enough space on the stack to call the runtime for the stack
3447 // overflow.
3448 Label done;
3449
3450 // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
3451 // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
3452 // check in the condition code.
3453 if (required_slots * kSystemPointerSize < v8_flags.stack_size * KB) {
3454 Register stack_limit = r1;
3455 __ LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
3456 __ AddS64(stack_limit, stack_limit,
3457 Operand(required_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
3458 __ CmpU64(sp, stack_limit);
3459 __ bge(&done);
3460 }
3461
3462 __ Call(static_cast<intptr_t>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
3463 RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
3464 // The call does not return, hence we can ignore any references and just
3465 // define an empty safepoint.
3466 ReferenceMap* reference_map = zone()->New<ReferenceMap>(zone());
3467 RecordSafepoint(reference_map);
3468 if (v8_flags.debug_code) __ stop();
3469
3470 __ bind(&done);
3471 }
3472#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3473
3474 // Skip callee-saved and return slots, which are pushed below.
3475 required_slots -= saves.Count();
3476 required_slots -= frame()->GetReturnSlotCount();
3477 required_slots -= (kDoubleSize / kSystemPointerSize) * saves_fp.Count();
3478 __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -required_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
3479 }
3480
3481 // Save callee-saved Double registers.
3482 if (!saves_fp.is_empty()) {
3483 __ MultiPushDoubles(saves_fp);
3484 DCHECK_EQ(kNumCalleeSavedDoubles, saves_fp.Count());
3485 }
3486
3487 // Save callee-saved registers.
3488 if (!saves.is_empty()) {
3489 __ MultiPush(saves);
3490 // register save area does not include the fp or constant pool pointer.
3491 }
3492
3493 const int returns = frame()->GetReturnSlotCount();
3494 // Create space for returns.
3495 __ AllocateStackSpace(returns * kSystemPointerSize);
3496
3497 if (!frame()->tagged_slots().IsEmpty()) {
3498 __ mov(kScratchReg, Operand(0));
3499 for (int spill_slot : frame()->tagged_slots()) {
3500 FrameOffset offset = frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(spill_slot);
3501 DCHECK(offset.from_frame_pointer());
3502 __ StoreU64(kScratchReg, MemOperand(fp, offset.offset()));
3503 }
3504 }
3505}

3507void CodeGenerator::AssembleReturn(InstructionOperand* additional_pop_count) {
3508 auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
3509
3510 const int returns = frame()->GetReturnSlotCount();
3511 if (returns != 0) {
3512 // Create space for returns.
3513 __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, returns * kSystemPointerSize));
3514 }
3515
3516 // Restore registers.
3517 const RegList saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters();
3518 if (!saves.is_empty()) {
3519 __ MultiPop(saves);
3520 }
3521
3522 // Restore double registers.
3523 const DoubleRegList double_saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters();
3524 if (!double_saves.is_empty()) {
3525 __ MultiPopDoubles(double_saves);
3526 }
3527
3528 unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
3529
3530 S390OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3531 const int parameter_slots =
3532 static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount());
3533
3534 // {aditional_pop_count} is only greater than zero if {parameter_slots = 0}.
3535 // Check RawMachineAssembler::PopAndReturn.
3536 if (parameter_slots != 0) {
3537 if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate()) {
3538 DCHECK_EQ(g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32(), 0);
3539 } else if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3540 __ CmpS64(g.ToRegister(additional_pop_count), Operand(0));
3541 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedAdditionalPopValue);
3542 }
3543 }
3544
3545 Register argc_reg = r5;
3546 // Functions with JS linkage have at least one parameter (the receiver).
3547 // If {parameter_slots} == 0, it means it is a builtin with
3548 // kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel, which takes care of JS arguments popping
3549 // itself.
3550 const bool drop_jsargs = parameter_slots != 0 &&
3551 frame_access_state()->has_frame() &&
3552 call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall();
3553
3554 if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
3555 AssembleDeconstructFrame();
3556 } else if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
3557 // Canonicalize JSFunction return sites for now unless they have an variable
3558 // number of stack slot pops
3559 if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate() &&
3560 g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32() == 0) {
3561 if (return_label_.is_bound()) {
3562 __ b(&return_label_);
3563 return;
3564 } else {
3565 __ bind(&return_label_);
3566 }
3567 }
3568 if (drop_jsargs) {
3569 // Get the actual argument count.
3570 DCHECK(!call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters().has(argc_reg));
3571 __ LoadU64(argc_reg, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
3572 }
3573 AssembleDeconstructFrame();
3574 }
3575
3576 if (drop_jsargs) {
3577 // We must pop all arguments from the stack (including the receiver).
3578 // The number of arguments without the receiver is
3579 // max(argc_reg, parameter_slots-1), and the receiver is added in
3580 // DropArguments().
3581 DCHECK(!call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters().has(argc_reg));
3582 if (parameter_slots > 1) {
3583 Label skip;
3584 __ CmpS64(argc_reg, Operand(parameter_slots));
3585 __ bgt(&skip);
3586 __ mov(argc_reg, Operand(parameter_slots));
3587 __ bind(&skip);
3588 }
3589 __ DropArguments(argc_reg);
3590 } else if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate()) {
3591 int additional_count = g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32();
3592 __ Drop(parameter_slots + additional_count);
3593 } else if (parameter_slots == 0) {
3594 __ Drop(g.ToRegister(additional_pop_count));
3595 } else {
3596 // {additional_pop_count} is guaranteed to be zero if {parameter_slots !=
3597 // 0}. Check RawMachineAssembler::PopAndReturn.
3598 __ Drop(parameter_slots);
3599 }
3600 __ Ret();
3601}

3608AllocatedOperand CodeGenerator::Push(InstructionOperand* source) {
3609 auto rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
3610 int new_slots = ElementSizeInPointers(rep);
3611 S390OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3612 int last_frame_slot_id =
3613 frame_access_state_->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - 1;
3614 int sp_delta = frame_access_state_->sp_delta();
3615 int slot_id = last_frame_slot_id + sp_delta + new_slots;
3616 AllocatedOperand stack_slot(LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep, slot_id);
3617 if (source->IsFloatStackSlot() || source->IsDoubleStackSlot()) {
3618 __ LoadU64(r1, g.ToMemOperand(source));
3619 __ Push(r1);
3620 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
3621 } else {
3622 // Bump the stack pointer and assemble the move.
3623 __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -(new_slots * kSystemPointerSize)));
3624 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
3625 AssembleMove(source, &stack_slot);
3626 }
3627 temp_slots_ += new_slots;
3628 return stack_slot;
3629}
3630
3631void CodeGenerator::Pop(InstructionOperand* dest, MachineRepresentation rep) {
3632 int dropped_slots = ElementSizeInPointers(rep);
3633 S390OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3634 if (dest->IsFloatStackSlot() || dest->IsDoubleStackSlot()) {
3635 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
3636 __ Pop(r1);
3637 __ StoreU64(r1, g.ToMemOperand(dest));
3638 } else {
3639 int last_frame_slot_id =
3640 frame_access_state_->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - 1;
3641 int sp_delta = frame_access_state_->sp_delta();
3642 int slot_id = last_frame_slot_id + sp_delta;
3643 AllocatedOperand stack_slot(LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep, slot_id);
3644 AssembleMove(&stack_slot, dest);
3645 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
3646 __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, dropped_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
3647 }
3648 temp_slots_ -= dropped_slots;
3649}
3650
3651void CodeGenerator::PopTempStackSlots() {
3652 if (temp_slots_ > 0) {
3653 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-temp_slots_);
3654 __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, temp_slots_ * kSystemPointerSize));
3655 temp_slots_ = 0;
3656 }
3657}

3659void CodeGenerator::MoveToTempLocation(InstructionOperand* source,
3660 MachineRepresentation rep) {
3661 // Must be kept in sync with {MoveTempLocationTo}.
3662 if (!IsFloatingPoint(rep) ||
3663 ((IsFloatingPoint(rep) &&
3664 !move_cycle_.pending_double_scratch_register_use))) {
3665 // The scratch register for this rep is available.
3666 int scratch_reg_code =
3667 !IsFloatingPoint(rep) ? kScratchReg.code() : kScratchDoubleReg.code();
3668 AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER, rep, scratch_reg_code);
3669 DCHECK(!AreAliased(kScratchReg, r0, r1));
3670 AssembleMove(source, &scratch);
3671 } else {
3672 // The scratch register is blocked by pending moves. Use the stack instead.
3673 Push(source);
3674 }
3675}
3676
3677void CodeGenerator::MoveTempLocationTo(InstructionOperand* dest,
3678 MachineRepresentation rep) {
3679 if (!IsFloatingPoint(rep) ||
3680 ((IsFloatingPoint(rep) &&
3681 !move_cycle_.pending_double_scratch_register_use))) {
3682 int scratch_reg_code =
3683 !IsFloatingPoint(rep) ? kScratchReg.code() : kScratchDoubleReg.code();
3684 AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER, rep, scratch_reg_code);
3685 DCHECK(!AreAliased(kScratchReg, r0, r1));
3686 AssembleMove(&scratch, dest);
3687 } else {
3688 Pop(dest, rep);
3689 }
3690 move_cycle_ = MoveCycleState();
3691}

3699
3700void CodeGenerator::AssembleMove(InstructionOperand* source,
3701 InstructionOperand* destination) {
3702 S390OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3703 // Dispatch on the source and destination operand kinds. Not all
3704 // combinations are possible.
3705 // If a move type needs the scratch register, this also needs to be recorded
3706 // in {SetPendingMove} to avoid conflicts with the gap resolver.
3707 if (source->IsRegister()) {
3708 DCHECK(destination->IsRegister() || destination->IsStackSlot());
3709 Register src = g.ToRegister(source);
3710 if (destination->IsRegister()) {
3711 __ Move(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
3712 } else {
3713 __ StoreU64(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3714 }
3715 } else if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
3716 DCHECK(destination->IsRegister() || destination->IsStackSlot());
3717 MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source);
3718 if (destination->IsRegister()) {
3719 __ LoadU64(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
3720 } else {
3721 Register temp = r1;
3722 __ LoadU64(temp, src, r0);
3723 __ StoreU64(temp, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3724 }
3725 } else if (source->IsConstant()) {
3726 Constant src = g.ToConstant(source);
3727 if (destination->IsRegister() || destination->IsStackSlot()) {
3728 Register dst = destination->IsRegister() ? g.ToRegister(destination) : r1;
3729 switch (src.type()) {
3730 case Constant::kInt32:
3731 __ mov(dst, Operand(src.ToInt32(), src.rmode()));
3732 break;
3733 case Constant::kInt64:
3734 __ mov(dst, Operand(src.ToInt64(), src.rmode()));
3735 break;
3736 case Constant::kFloat32:
3737 __ mov(dst, Operand::EmbeddedNumber(src.ToFloat32()));
3738 break;
3739 case Constant::kFloat64:
3740 __ mov(dst, Operand::EmbeddedNumber(src.ToFloat64().value()));
3741 break;
3742 case Constant::kExternalReference:
3743 __ Move(dst, src.ToExternalReference());
3744 break;
3745 case Constant::kHeapObject: {
3746 Handle<HeapObject> src_object = src.ToHeapObject();
3747 RootIndex index;
3748 if (IsMaterializableFromRoot(src_object, &index)) {
3749 __ LoadRoot(dst, index);
3750 } else {
3751 __ Move(dst, src_object);
3752 }
3753 break;
3754 }
3755 case Constant::kCompressedHeapObject: {
3756 Handle<HeapObject> src_object = src.ToHeapObject();
3757 RootIndex index;
3758 if (IsMaterializableFromRoot(src_object, &index)) {
3759 __ LoadTaggedRoot(dst, index);
3760 } else {
3761 __ Move(dst, src_object, RelocInfo::COMPRESSED_EMBEDDED_OBJECT);
3762 }
3763 break;
3764 }
3765 case Constant::kRpoNumber:
3766 UNREACHABLE(); // TODO(dcarney): loading RPO constants on S390.
3767 }
3768 if (destination->IsStackSlot()) {
3769 __ StoreU64(dst, g.ToMemOperand(destination), r0);
3770 }
3771 } else {
3772 DoubleRegister dst = destination->IsFPRegister()
3773 ? g.ToDoubleRegister(destination)
3774 : kScratchDoubleReg;
3775 double value = (src.type() == Constant::kFloat32)
3776 ? src.ToFloat32()
3777 : src.ToFloat64().value();
3778 if (src.type() == Constant::kFloat32) {
3779 __ LoadF32<float>(dst, src.ToFloat32(), r1);
3780 } else {
3781 __ LoadF64<double>(dst, value, r1);
3782 }
3783
3784 if (destination->IsFloatStackSlot()) {
3785 __ StoreF32(dst, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3786 } else if (destination->IsDoubleStackSlot()) {
3787 __ StoreF64(dst, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3788 }
3789 }
3790 } else if (source->IsFPRegister()) {
3791 MachineRepresentation rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
3792 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
3793 if (destination->IsSimd128Register()) {
3794 __ vlr(g.ToSimd128Register(destination), g.ToSimd128Register(source),
3795 Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
3796 } else {
3797 DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128StackSlot());
3798 __ StoreV128(g.ToSimd128Register(source), g.ToMemOperand(destination),
3799 r1);
3800 }
3801 } else {
3802 DoubleRegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
3803 if (destination->IsFPRegister()) {
3804 DoubleRegister dst = g.ToDoubleRegister(destination);
3805 __ Move(dst, src);
3806 } else {
3807 DCHECK(destination->IsFPStackSlot());
3808 LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(source);
3809 if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
3810 __ StoreF64(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3811 } else {
3812 __ StoreF32(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3813 }
3814 }
3815 }
3816 } else if (source->IsFPStackSlot()) {
3817 DCHECK(destination->IsFPRegister() || destination->IsFPStackSlot());
3818 MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source);
3819 if (destination->IsFPRegister()) {
3820 LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(source);
3821 if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
3822 __ LoadF64(g.ToDoubleRegister(destination), src);
3823 } else if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
3824 __ LoadF32(g.ToDoubleRegister(destination), src);
3825 } else {
3826 DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, op->representation());
3827 __ LoadV128(g.ToSimd128Register(destination), g.ToMemOperand(source),
3828 r1);
3829 }
3830 } else {
3831 LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(source);
3832 DoubleRegister temp = kScratchDoubleReg;
3833 if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
3834 __ LoadF64(temp, src);
3835 __ StoreF64(temp, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3836 } else if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
3837 __ LoadF32(temp, src);
3838 __ StoreF32(temp, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3839 } else {
3840 DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, op->representation());
3841 __ LoadV128(kScratchDoubleReg, g.ToMemOperand(source), r1);
3842 __ StoreV128(kScratchDoubleReg, g.ToMemOperand(destination), r1);
3843 }
3844 }
3845 } else {
3846 UNREACHABLE();
3847 }
3848}
3849
3850// Swaping contents in source and destination.
3851// source and destination could be:
3852// Register,
3853// FloatRegister,
3854// DoubleRegister,
3855// StackSlot,
3856// FloatStackSlot,
3857// or DoubleStackSlot
3858void CodeGenerator::AssembleSwap(InstructionOperand* source,
3859 InstructionOperand* destination) {
3860 S390OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3861 if (source->IsRegister()) {
3862 Register src = g.ToRegister(source);
3863 if (destination->IsRegister()) {
3864 __ SwapP(src, g.ToRegister(destination), kScratchReg);
3865 } else {
3866 DCHECK(destination->IsStackSlot());
3867 __ SwapP(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination), kScratchReg);
3868 }
3869 } else if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
3870 DCHECK(destination->IsStackSlot());
3871 __ SwapP(g.ToMemOperand(source), g.ToMemOperand(destination), kScratchReg,
3872 r0);
3873 } else if (source->IsFloatRegister()) {
3874 DoubleRegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
3875 if (destination->IsFloatRegister()) {
3876 __ SwapFloat32(src, g.ToDoubleRegister(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
3877 } else {
3878 DCHECK(destination->IsFloatStackSlot());
3879 __ SwapFloat32(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
3880 }
3881 } else if (source->IsDoubleRegister()) {
3882 DoubleRegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
3883 if (destination->IsDoubleRegister()) {
3884 __ SwapDouble(src, g.ToDoubleRegister(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
3885 } else {
3886 DCHECK(destination->IsDoubleStackSlot());
3887 __ SwapDouble(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
3888 }
3889 } else if (source->IsFloatStackSlot()) {
3890 DCHECK(destination->IsFloatStackSlot());
3891 __ SwapFloat32(g.ToMemOperand(source), g.ToMemOperand(destination),
3892 kScratchDoubleReg);
3893 } else if (source->IsDoubleStackSlot()) {
3894 DCHECK(destination->IsDoubleStackSlot());
3895 __ SwapDouble(g.ToMemOperand(source), g.ToMemOperand(destination),
3896 kScratchDoubleReg);
3897 } else if (source->IsSimd128Register()) {
3898 Simd128Register src = g.ToSimd128Register(source);
3899 if (destination->IsSimd128Register()) {
3900 __ SwapSimd128(src, g.ToSimd128Register(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
3901 } else {
3902 DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128StackSlot());
3903 __ SwapSimd128(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
3904 }
3905 } else if (source->IsSimd128StackSlot()) {
3906 DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128StackSlot());
3907 __ SwapSimd128(g.ToMemOperand(source), g.ToMemOperand(destination),
3908 kScratchDoubleReg);
3909 } else {
3910 UNREACHABLE();
3911 }
3912}
